ature-discussion (RFC)\r\n\r\n* CakePHP Version: 4.2.6 - 243a54d83438d9e9d5e3f4ccc1e379dcd20b5a38\r\n* Platform and Target: PHP 7.4.9 CLI\r\n\r\n### What you did\r\nWithin Application.php middleware I updated the CsrfProtectionMiddleware to use a custom cookie name, after this I reran my unit tests and found all POST requests were failing with 'Cake\\Http\\Exception\\InvalidCsrfTokenException: Missing or incorrect CSRF cookie type.'.\r\n\r\nApplication.php\r\n```\r\npublic function middleware(MiddlewareQueue $middlewareQueue): MiddlewareQueue\r\n{\r\n    ...\r\n\r\n    // Cross Site Request Forgery (CSRF) Protection Middleware\r\n    ->add(new CsrfProtectionMiddleware([\r\n        'httponly' => true,\r\n        'secure' => true,\r\n        'cookieName' => '__Secure-myapp-csrfToken',\r\n        'samesite' => 'Strict',\r\n    ]))\r\n```\r\n\r\nForgotControllerTest.php\r\n```\r\nclass ForgotControllerTest extends IntegrationTestCase\r\n{\r\n    public function setUp(): void\r\n    {\r\n        parent::setUp();\r\n        $this->disableErrorHandlerMiddleware();\r\n        $this->enableCsrfToken();\r\n        $this->enableSecurityToken();\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    public function testResetPassword()\r\n    {\r\n        $data = [\r\n            'email' => 'test@test.com',\r\n        ];\r\n        $this->post('/forgot/reset-password/myguid', $data);\r\n        $this->assertResponseOk();\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### What happened\r\nSetting a custom cookie name within CsrfProtectionMiddleware is causing unit tests to fail with 'Cake\\Http\\Exception\\InvalidCsrfTokenException: Missing or incorrect CSRF cookie type.'.\r\n\r\nUsing the default cookie name of 'csrfToken' allows the tests to pass as expected.\r\n\r\n### What you expected to happen\r\nI expected the IntegrationTestTrait to use the custom cookie name when setting tokens with the enableCsrfToken() function.\r\n\r\nFrom my initial investigation I have found the IntegrationTestTrait.php is using a hardcoded cookie name 